Graph doesn't necessarily need to contain a list of Edges/nodes. It contains graph algorithms. You construct it with a Node and
it figures out the structure from that node's connectivity.
Edges and Nodes can exist without a graph class holding them.
1. Deleting an Edge: Node::RemoveEdge() handles it.
2. Deleting an Atom: Everthing auto except Node destructor calls incoming neighbors
and updates their outNode list to remove unlockable Target Nodes. Once Node
destructor is triggered weak_ptrs to that Node no longer lock.
